text: The name Jenny has been used for one tropical cyclone in the Atlantic Ocean. * Tropical Storm Jenny (1969) – a weak tropical storm which affected Cuba and the U.S. Gulf Coast. The name Jenny has been used in the Philippines by PAGASA in the Western Pacific. * Typhoon Dujuan (2015) (T1521, 21W, Jenny) – a powerful typhoon which struck the Ryukyu Islands and Taiwan. * Tropical Storm Podul (2019) (T1912, 13W, Jenny)- an active disorganized tropical storm which caused flooding in the rain-battered Philippines.
